• Technique for Order Preference by Similarity to Ideal Solution (TOPSIS)

TOPSIS is an aggregating compensatory method based on the concept that the chosen solution should have the shortest geometric distance from the positive ideal solution [33], [39] and the longest geometric distance from the negative ideal solution. The TOPSIS method consists mainly of these actions: normalizing the data, computing the geometric distance between each alternative and the ideal alternative. The TOPSIS process is as follows:

