number of the decision criteria.

• Weighted Product Model (WPM)

WPM called also Multiplicative Exponential Weighting (MEW) is similar to SAW, [33], [41].

The dierence is the replacement of the addition operation in SAW with the multiplication

operation in WPM; each decision alternative is compared with the others ones by multiplying

a number of ratios, one for each decision criterion. Each ratio is raised to the power equivalent

to the relative weight of the corresponding criterion. The mathematical description is as

follows: n

