• Analytical Hierarchy Process AHP

AHP considers the decomposition of a complicated problem into multiple hierarchical simple sub-problems [33]. The AHP steps are as follows:

- First, decompose the problem to set hierarchical sub-problems, where the top node is the nal goal and in the lower nodes are the alternative solutions to the problem.

- Second, determination of the relative importance of the criteria with respect to the objective. In each level the decision factors are compared pairwise according to their levels of inuence with respect to the scale shown in Table 3.1.

- Third, calculating the weights in all the hierarchy levels.

- Fourth, the AHP method in general is coupled with Grey Relational Analysis (GRA) to rank alternatives.

